    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering a pristine 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD, a masterclass in longitudinal front-midship engineering. This example features the sequential twin-turbocharged 13B-REW rotary engine, exhibiting exceptional compression across all rotor faces. The factory-spec sequential boost transition remains seamless, supported by a preventative Viton vacuum line refresh. The chassis retains its original double-wishbone suspension with aluminum control arms, providing telepathic turn-in. Power is delivered through a precise 5-speed manual to a Torsen limited-slip differential. This is a zero-oxidation, turn-key specimen with original paint depth and a flawless interior, catering to the most discerning JDM purist.",
